# Stage D Static Demo

Active until Stage 0 Next.js replaces client preview. Read [docs/architecture/stage-demo-static.md](../../docs/architecture/stage-demo-static.md) before editing `demo/`.

## Plan before execute

1. State what changes (copy, images, new page) and what stays untouched (grid CSS, card HTML shape).
2. Edit `demo/js/messages.js` for copy (ES + EN); keep `data-i18n` keys on visible text.
3. Run `npm run demo:build-check` before suggesting Netlify deploy.

## Product card HTML (do not break)

Every `.product-card` inside `.product-grid` must keep this shape:

```html
<!-- GOOD -->
<article class="product-card" data-team="..." data-liga="..." data-price="...">
  <a href="/products/....html">
    <span class="product-badge">...</span>  <!-- optional -->
    <div class="product-image">
      <div class="placeholder-jersey has-photo" style="background-image:url('/images/....')">Jersey</div>
    </div>
    <div class="product-info">
      <h3>Product title</h3>
      <p class="product-price">$ X,XXX.00</p>
    </div>
  </a>
</article>
```

```html
<!-- BAD: breaks grid proportions -->
<div class="product-image"><img src="/images/jersey1.webp" alt="..."></div>
<!-- BAD: missing product-info wrapper -->
<div class="product-image">...</div>
<p class="product-price">...</p>
```

## Images in demo

| Location | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `demo/images/` | Jersey photos served at `/images/*` on Netlify (publish dir is `demo/`) |
| `images/` (repo root) | Optional staging only; copy into `demo/images/` before deploy |
| `demo/assets/` | Logo and brand static files |

- Use `background-image` on `.placeholder-jersey.has-photo`, not full-bleed `<img>` in cards.
- PDP gallery: keep `.placeholder-jersey` inside `.pdp-gallery-main` and `.pdp-thumb` (see `demo/js/demo.js` `initGallery`).
- Do not add CSS that sets product images to `width:100%;height:100%` on placeholders unless scoped to PDP only.

## Copy and markets

- Decoration types (bordado, DTF, TPU, 3D DTF) are available for **Mexico and US** unless product owner says otherwise.
- Do not split finishing by market in UI copy without explicit approval.
- Avoid duplicate hero sections that repeat the same CTA (one primary path to `/custom/uniform.html`).

## Deploy

- Stage D: `publish = "demo"` in root `netlify.toml`; deploy with `npx netlify deploy --prod --dir=demo`.
- Zip deploy: `npm run demo:package` (POSIX paths; never Windows `Compress-Archive`).
- Stage 0 app (`app/`) uses `@netlify/plugin-nextjs`; do not mix publish dirs in one deploy.
